trans-unit.source: Provides a standard set of component-related commands, which have predefined key input gestures and <see cref="P:System.Windows.Input.RoutedUICommand.Text" /> properties.

The commands in the <xref:System.Windows.Input.ComponentCommands> class and commands in the other command library classes, such as <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands> and <xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands>, are intended to represent a set of common commands that application programmers encounter frequently.
trans-unit.target: 中的命令<xref:System.Windows.Input.ComponentCommands>类和另一部分中的命令命令库类，如<xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands>和<xref:System.Windows.Input.NavigationCommands>，用于表示一组的应用程序程序员经常遇到的常见命令。

trans-unit.source: The commands only represent the instance of the <xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand> and not the implementation logic for the command.
trans-unit.target: 命令仅表示的实例<xref:System.Windows.Input.RoutedCommand>不实现逻辑的命令。

trans-unit.source: The implementation logic is bound to the command via a <xref:System.Windows.UIElement.CommandBindings%2A>.

For example, if the <xref:System.Windows.Input.ComponentCommands.MoveLeft%2A> command is executed on a control (the command target), the logic that performs the <xref:System.Windows.Input.ComponentCommands.MoveLeft%2A> command may not be provided by the command target, so the application writer is responsible for writing the logic that determines how the command target handles the command.
trans-unit.target: 例如，如果<xref:System.Windows.Input.ComponentCommands.MoveLeft%2A>控件 （命令目标），执行的逻辑上执行命令<xref:System.Windows.Input.ComponentCommands.MoveLeft%2A>命令可能无法提供命令目标，因此应用程序编写器负责编写逻辑，用于确定如何命令目标处理命令。

trans-unit.source: Many controls do provide implementation logic, though, for many of the commands in the command library.
trans-unit.target: 许多控件提供实现逻辑，不过，对于许多命令库中的命令。

trans-unit.source: For example, the <xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox> class provides logic for the <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Paste%2A> command, <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Cut%2A> command, <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Copy%2A> command, <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Undo%2A> command, and <xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Redo%2A> command.
trans-unit.target: 例如，<xref:System.Windows.Controls.TextBox>类提供了逻辑<xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Paste%2A>命令，<xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Cut%2A>命令，<xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Copy%2A>命令，<xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Undo%2A>命令，和<xref:System.Windows.Input.ApplicationCommands.Redo%2A>命令。

trans-unit.source: See the class documentation for particular control classes for more information.
trans-unit.target: 请参阅有关详细信息的特定控件类的类文档。

trans-unit.source: For more information on commands and commanding, see [Commanding Overview](~/docs/framework/wpf/advanced/commanding-overview.md).
trans-unit.target: 有关命令和命令的详细信息，请参阅[命令概述](~/docs/framework/wpf/advanced/commanding-overview.md)。

trans-unit.source: Gets the value that represents the Extend Selection Down command.
This command indicates the intention to extend the selection downward.
trans-unit.target: 此命令指示打算将选择向下扩展。

trans-unit.source: There is not necessarily an actual implementation responding to the command on any given object; in many cases the implementation in response to that command is the responsibility of the application writer.
trans-unit.target: 并不一定对任何给定的对象; 上的命令的响应的实际实现在许多情况下对该命令的响应中的实现是应用程序编写器的责任。
